aVSo what happens when we take the same data
p239
aVbut we use different sets of puzzle pieces to reconstruct the image?
p240
aVLet's first start with black hole image simulation puzzle pieces.
p241
aVOK, this looks reasonable.
p242
aVThis looks like what we expect a black hole to look like.
p243
aVBut did we just get it
p244
aVbecause we just fed it little pieces of black hole simulation images?
p245
aVLet's try another set of puzzle pieces
p246
aVfrom astronomical, non-black hole objects.
p247
aVOK, we get a similar-looking image.
p248
aVAnd then how about pieces from everyday images,
p249
aVlike the images you take with your own personal camera?
p250
aVGreat, we see the same image.
p251
aVWhen we get the same image from all different sets of puzzle pieces,
p252
aVthen we can start to become more confident
p253
aVthat the image assumptions we're making
p254
aVaren't biasing the final image we get too much.
p255
aa(lp256
VAnother thing we can do is take the same set of puzzle pieces,
p257
aVsuch as the ones derived from everyday images,
p258
aVand use them to reconstruct many different kinds of source images.
p259
aVSo in our simulations,
p260
aVwe pretend a black hole looks like astronomical non-black hole objects,
p261
aVas well as everyday images like the elephant in the center of our galaxy.
p262
aVWhen the results of our algorithms on the bottom look very similar
p263
aVto the simulation's truth image on top,
p264
aVthen we can start to become more confident in our algorithms.
p265
aVAnd I really want to emphasize here
p266
aVthat all of these pictures were created
p267
aVby piecing together little pieces of everyday photographs,
p268
aVlike you'd take with your own personal camera.
p269
aVSo an image of a black hole we've never seen before
p270
aVmay eventually be created by piecing together pictures we see all the time
p271
aVof people, buildings, trees, cats and dogs.
p272
aVImaging ideas like this will make it possible for us
p273
aVto take our very first pictures of a black hole,
p274
aVand hopefully, verify those famous theories
p275
aVon which scientists rely on a daily basis.
